  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nWe have a situations when were machine is weak (especially disk) then we can stuck on State Sync - but this should also result with slow SnapSync.\r\nI have a situation where Snap took about 3h, but StateSync is already at 5h and is unable to progress.\r\n\r\nI have noticed, that after restart, \"Downloaded\" was like 300-400 blocks behind which should not happen since we are syncing blocks (HEAD-32) for the time when Snap and State syncs are in progress.\r\n\r\nAttaching logs before restart and after restart.\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Ubuntu\r\n - Chain: Mainnet\r\n - Version master\r\n\r\n**Logs**\r\nHere are Debug logs before restarting BUT those are very verbose and are automatically truncated so having only a few ones\r\n[mainnet before.zip](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/10231568/mainnet.before.zip)\r\n\r\nAnd those are after restarting\r\n[mainnet after.zip](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/files/10231569/mainnet.after.zip)\r\n",
